{"flatpakAppId":"org.gnome.Games","name":"Games","summary":"Simple game launcher for GNOME","description":"\n    <p>\n      Games is a GNOME 3 application to browse your video games library and to\n      easily pick and play a game from it. It aims to do for games what Music\n      already does for your music library.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      You want to install Games if you just want a very simple and comfortable\n      way to play your games and you don’t need advanced features such as\n      speedrunning tools or video game development tools.\n    </p>\n    <p>Features:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>List your installed games, your Steam games, your game ROMs…</li>\n      <li>Search in your games collection</li>\n      <li>Play your games</li>\n      <li>Resume your game to where you left it</li>\n    </ul>\n  ","developerName":"The GNOME Project","projectLicense":"GPL-3.0+","homepageUrl":"https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Games","donationUrl":"http://www.gnome.org/friends/","translateUrl":"https://wiki.gnome.org/TranslationProject","bugtrackerUrl":"https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-games/issues","helpUrl":null,"categories":[{"name":"Player"},{"name":"Game"}],"downloadFlatpakRefUrl":"gnome-games-app","currentReleaseVersion":"40.0","currentReleaseDescription":null,"iconDesktopUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jammy/org/gnome/Games/5c2cea88ad88693ec0dfaf59ff27da1b/icons/128x128/gnome-games-app_org.gnome.Games.png","iconMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jammy/org/gnome/Games/5c2cea88ad88693ec0dfaf59ff27da1b/icons/128x128/gnome-games-app_org.gnome.Games.png","screenshots":[{"thumbUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jammy/org/gnome/Games/5c2cea88ad88693ec0dfaf59ff27da1b/screenshots/image-1_224x136.png","imgMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jammy/org/gnome/Games/5c2cea88ad88693ec0dfaf59ff27da1b/screenshots/image-1_1248x762.png","imgDesktopUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jammy/org/gnome/Games/5c2cea88ad88693ec0dfaf59ff27da1b/screen